  "text": "The Niagara Query Engine uses two implementations for the join operator: nested loops and symmetric hash join [CITATION_1] . The symmetric hash join implementation is more appropriate for queries over data streams since it does not block on either input. We implement symmetric hash join using one hash Table 4 . If a punctuation arrives from one input specifying that all tuples have arrived for a particular set of join attribute values, then we remove tuples from the hash table for the other input using the join values described by the punctuation as the hash key.",
